{# Message triage prompt — lightweight inbox processing.
   Variables: msg_count, messages_text, agent_id
#}
You have {{ msg_count }} unread message(s) in your inbox. Triage them.

## Messages

{{ messages_text }}

## What to Do

For each message, decide:

1. **Urgent / actionable** — the message explicitly requests immediate work or flags something broken. Create a task in the tasks/queued/ directory assigned to the right agent (which may be yourself). This should be rare — most messages are not urgent.
2. **Informational** — the message shares perspective, context, or a suggestion to factor into your ongoing work. Update your working memory at agents/state/{{ agent_id }}/working-memory.md so you'll consider it during your next drive consultation or task. This is the most common category. Messages from the human operator are usually this — direction and perspective, not orders.
3. **Acknowledged** — the message doesn't require action or memory. Just note it in your log.

After processing each message, move it to processed by calling the bash command:
```bash
mv {message_path} {message_path_parent}/processed/
```
Make sure the processed/ directory exists first (mkdir -p).

Be concise. This is triage, not deep work. Read, decide, act, move on.
